, psychosocial, intercultural, collaborative, and interactive systems dimensions of what it means to sustain our common future together. The 3C cartography examines the less tangible human behaviors, thoughts and emotions, worldviews, interdependencies, complexities, and dynamic adaptability that factor into climate change and its threats to human and other-than-human life on earth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Cultural Anthropology. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Psychology. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Sociology. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Studies. 7aEDUCATION / Teaching Methods & Materials / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2024z978311149259940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849696240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438496962423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438496962/original  a978-3-11-149259-9  SUNY Press eBook Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles